<div class="section" id="money">
<h2>7. Getting Paid</h2>

<h3>Payment methods to set up</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Method</th><th>Best For</th><th>Fees</th><th>Setup</th></tr>
  <tr><td>PayPal</td><td>Most common on Reddit</td><td>~3%</td><td><a class="url" href="https://paypal.com">paypal.com</a></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Wise</td><td>International clients, low fees</td><td>~1%</td><td><a class="url" href="https://wise.com">wise.com</a></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Revolut</td><td>Fast, good for Europe</td><td>Low</td><td><a class="url" href="https://revolut.com">revolut.com</a></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Crypto (USDC)</td><td>Some Reddit users prefer</td><td>~0%</td><td>Coinbase/Binance</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="warning">‚ö†Ô∏è NEVER send the full deliverable before receiving payment. Always collect payment first, or use a screenshot/preview as proof.</div>

<h3>Pricing tips</h3>
<div class="step">
  <div style="font-size:12px;line-height:2.2;color:var(--text2)">
    ‚Ä¢ If post says $10 ‚Üí accept it, good for low effort<br/>
    ‚Ä¢ If post says $20-50 ‚Üí sweet spot, accept it<br/>
    ‚Ä¢ If post says $50+ ‚Üí accept it, AI can handle it<br/>
    ‚Ä¢ If no price listed ‚Üí reply asking for budget first<br/>
    ‚Ä¢ Never undercut yourself ‚Äî your time reviewing is worth something too
  </div>
</div>
</div>

